HEADWORD: Transpass
<hw>Trans*pass"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>trans-</ets> + <ets>pass</ets>: cf. LL. <ets>transpassare</ets>.
Cf. <er>Trespass</er>.]</ety> <def>To pass over; <as>as, Alexander
<ex>transpassed</ex> the river</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>J. Gregory.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transpass</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transpass
<hw>Trans*pass"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To pass by; to pass
away.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transpassable</ent>⟦br⟧
